# Lab 5: Memory Pool Allocator

Implement a fixed-size memory pool:

```c
#define POOL_SIZE 8
#define BLOCK_SIZE 16

typedef struct {
    uint8_t  blocks[POOL_SIZE][BLOCK_SIZE];
    uint8_t  used[POOL_SIZE];  // 0=free, 1=used
    uint8_t  alloc_count;      // total allocations
    uint8_t  free_count;       // total frees
} MemPool;

void*   pool_alloc(MemPool* p);
void    pool_free(MemPool* p, void* ptr);
uint8_t pool_used_count(const MemPool* p);
uint8_t pool_free_count(const MemPool* p);
```

Test:
1. Allocate 4 blocks — verify used_count=4
2. Free block 1 and 3 — verify used_count=2
3. Allocate again — verify reuse of freed blocks
4. Try allocate all 8 blocks — all succeed
5. Allocate 9th — returns NULL (pool exhausted)
6. Verify alloc_count and free_count tracking

